<!-- Add Activity -->
    <activity>
       <introduction>
         <p>
             In grade 10, we introduced logarithms and explored their relationship
             with exponents. We also learned about the properties of logarithms and how to evaluate logarithmic 
             expressions. In this section, we will review these concepts and build a strong foundation
              for solving logarithmic equations in the upcoming sections.
         </p>
       </introduction>
        
     <statement>
        <p>
            <term>Work in groups</term>
        </p>

        <p>
            <term>What you need</term>
        </p>

        <p>
            Cards with logarithmic expressions and equations
            Manila paper
            Markers
            Scientific calculators
            Sticky notes (optional)
        </p>

        <p>
            <term>What to do</term>
        </p>

        <task>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    Divide into groups and let each group receive a set of cards containing logarithmic expressions, laws of logarithms, and logarithmic equations.
                </p>

                <p>
                    Work together to simplify the expressions, apply the logarithm laws correctly, and solve the equations on the cards.
                </p>

                <p>
                    Record all solutions and working steps on the manila paper.
                </p>
            </statement>
        </task>

        <task>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    Discuss within your group which logarithm law was used in each question, such as the product law, quotient law, or power law.
                </p>
            </statement>
        </task>

        <task>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    Exchange your completed work with another group and check each other's solutions for accuracy and correct use of logarithm laws.
                </p>
            </statement>
        </task>

        <task>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    Identify and correct any mistakes found during the checking process and discuss the correct methods together as a class.
                </p>
            </statement>
        </task>

        <task>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    Present one solved question to the class and explain the steps used to obtain the solution.
                </p>
            </statement>
        </task>
     </statement>
</activity>
    
    
    
     <!-- Add insight / key takeaway directly related to activity / learner experience -->
